Waterfiends are demonic elemental monsters made entirely out of water, which can be located in Ghorrock fortress during and after the completion of The Temple at Senntisten. They are slightly weaker than the versions found in the Ancient Cavern. Additionally, they are aggressive monsters, whereas their counterparts are not. They are also completely immune to fire spells.

During the quest, they appear from inside various ice blocks when a heat globe is placed nearby. If the heat globe is subsequently removed, they will turn into icefiends. Likewise, the icefiends will turn back into waterfiends if the heat globe is placed back.

One unique, level 107 Waterfiend can be found frozen within a large ice block on the lower floor, alongside a crate that contains 40 law runes. Unlike the other waterfiends, it can be seen before it is unfrozen, and it cannot be turned into an icefiend. Although it has significantly more lifepoints than the other waterfiends, it is incapable of dealing damage with ranged attacks.

After the quest, the level 102 versions can be found in the bottom floor of the dungeon, with icefiends instead being found upstairs.
